glitz
-------------------------------------------
Glitz is an OpenGL image compositing library. Glitz provides
Porter/Duff compositing of images and implicit mask generation for
geometric primitives including trapezoids, triangles, and rectangles.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.5.19-4
  libGL1-6.4.2-1

Build requirements:
  cygwin-1.5.19-4
  autoconf2.5-2.59-3
  automake1.9-1.9.6-1
  binutils-20050610-1
  gawk-3.1.5-2
  gcc-core-3.4.4-1
  libtool1.5-1.5.20-2
  make-3.80-1
  sed-4.1.4-1
  xorg-x11-devel-6.8.2.0-1

Canonical homepage:
  http://cairographics.org/

Canonical download:
  http://cairographics.org/snapshots/

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack glitz-0.4.4-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  ./glitz-0.4.4-X.sh all

This will create:
  /usr/src/glitz-0.4.4-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/glitz-0.4.4-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libglitz1-0.4.4-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libglitz-glx1-0.4.4-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

  /usr/include/glitz-glx.h
  /usr/include/glitz.h
  /usr/lib/libglitz-glx.a
